  "id": "listless_inertia",
  "title": "The Weight of Stillness",
  "description": "Taking action feels like moving through molasses—every step requires monumental effort.",
  "content": "The to-do list sits untouched. The emails go unanswered. The projects languish half-finished. You tell yourself you'll start tomorrow, but tomorrow comes and goes with the same paralysis. It's not that you don't care—it's that caring doesn't translate into doing. The gap between intention and action has become a chasm. You watch others move through the world with ease, accomplishing things, making progress, and you can't figure out how they do it.",
