      "id": "tiny_action",
      "text": "Start with something ridiculously small",
      "description": "One tiny action beats infinite planning.",
      "resultText": "You give yourself permission to do the smallest possible thing—so small it feels almost pointless. Answer one email. Work for five minutes. Make the bed. The tininess of the task makes it achievable. And when you do it, something shifts. The next small thing becomes slightly easier. You're not suddenly driven, but you've proven to yourself that action is possible. Momentum, you discover, can start microscopic.",
